Hello, For M4.4 (hopefully), I've created a core improvement to the core code to allow the user to add custom CSS to the core H5P module.¬† This implementation is managed by MDL-79802 , so if you have a Tracker account and are a developer, then I'm looking for a peer reviewer please .¬† More information on https://moodledev.io/general/development/tracker and https://moodledev.io/general/development/process/peer-review . As an example, you could use the following CSS to make the titles in a presentation, pink: 
```text
.h5p-course-presentation h2,
.h5p-course-presentation .h5p-footer .h5p-footer-toggle-keywords .current-slide-title {
    color: #fab;
}
```
 Thanks, Gareth

I found there is a very similar discussion on the H5P site specific to their activity implementation. It is not difficult to set the specific icons from the core implementation. The main problem is that the H5P icons appear small in Moodle (as Stuart observed). The icons supplied by H5P are in a different format than Moodle icons. Moodle icons are expected to be square and without margins. H5P icons are 16:9 aspect and about 20% margins. That can be compensated for with CSS on the course page, but not in the grade book. The content bank icons look better with 
```text
.cb-toolbar-container .icon-size-4 .icon {


    width: 43px !important;


    margin: 0 -7px;


}
```
 added to the 'Raw SCSS' in Boost, but I do not think that is the best long term solution.
